Distribution.
S. thompsonii is
an epi-pelagic species with a world-wide oceanic distribution in warm and temperate regions. According to
Pillai ( 1973 )
it is the most widely distributed mysid in oceanic waters. It is known from the north-eastern region of Australia , in the Great Barrier Reef at Low Isles (
W.M. Tattersall 1936 a
) and at Davies Reef (
Carleton & Hamner 1989
). It has also been taken in New South Wales coastal water (
McWilliam & Phillips 1983
) and off the west coast of Western Australia (
Pillai 1973
).
